Tube / Triode Bias (even harmonic emphasis)                                                             
  - Basically all classic rock vocals: the Fairchild 670 compressor (tubes biased to add 2nd harmonic) is 
  on almost every Beatles vocal                                                                           
  - Al Green — "Let's Stay Together" (the warmth is tube console saturation at Royal Studios)             
  - Amy Winehouse — "Back to Black" (recorded through vintage Neve + tube gear specifically for that      
  coloration)                                                                                             
  - Any record mixed through an API or Neve console gets subtle triode-style even harmonics on every      
  channel      
